<h3 id="member2634883">Dr Jamie Wilson</h3>
<p><em>Founder  CEO</em></p>
<p>
</p><p>Hometouch founder and CEO Dr Jamie Wilson started his career as a dementia specialist at Imperial College. Frustrated with NHS bureaucracy and experiencing first hand how difficult it was for his patients to find reliable home care, he realised the agency model was broken: carers were paid minimum wage, and patients had a lack of choice and control regarding care provision. It was clear to Jamie that fixing the agency model trust was critical for the future of dementia care and the NHS. Jamie founded Hometouch in 2015 and has received more than Â£5m in financial backing from BUPA, the UK government and Passion capital.</p>
